---

# 📘 MULTITHREADING 

---

# 🧠 1️⃣ What is Thread?

## ✅ Definition

A **thread** is the smallest unit of execution inside a process.

👉 A program can have **multiple threads running simultaneously**

---

## 🌍 Real-world Example

* You are coding 💻
* Music playing 🎧
* Download running ⬇️

👉 All happening together → **Multithreading**

---

# 🎯 Why Multithreading?

* Faster execution 🚀
* Better CPU utilization
* Parallel processing

---

# 🧱 2️⃣ Process vs Thread (IMPORTANT)

| Process    | Thread        |
| ---------- | ------------- |
| Heavy      | Light         |
| Own memory | Shared memory |
| Slow       | Fast          |

---

# 🧰 3️⃣ Ways to Create Thread

---

## 🔹 1. Extend Thread class

```java
class MyThread extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        System.out.println("Thread running");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        MyThread t = new MyThread();
        t.start();
    }
}
```

---

## 🔹 2. Implement Runnable (BEST PRACTICE 🔥)

```java
class MyTask implements Runnable {
    public void run() {
        System.out.println("Running...");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Thread t = new Thread(new MyTask());
        t.start();
    }
}
```

---

# 🔥 Interview Question

👉 Which is better?
👉 **Runnable** (because Java supports single inheritance)

